 As his tenure ends midnight of Monday, 15th of October, 2018, the outgoing Ekiti State Governor, Ayodele Fayose, has left the town Sunday afternoon, promising the people that he will always be with them. He was reported to have also urged them to trust in God for a better future for him and the state. He stated this during a thanksgiving service held in his honour at the Government House Chapel on Sunday morning, after which he left the state. Many of the residents were reportedly shedding tears while lining up the streets to bid him farewell on his way to the Akure Airport, Ondo State. 